{
  "local_port": 36748,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the process of securing admission at MICA, Ahmedabad?",
  "response": "Securing admission to MICA (Mudra Institute of Communications, Ahmedabad) involves a multi-step process that evaluates candidates based on their academic background, entrance exam scores, and performance in group activities and interviews. Below is a detailed overview of the admission process for MICA's postgraduate programs, primarily the PGDM-C (Post Graduate Diploma in Management - Communications):\n\n---\n\n### **1. Eligibility Criteria**\n- **Academic Qualification**: Candidates must have a bachelor's degree (10+2+3 system) in any discipline from a recognized university.\n- **Minimum Marks**: Generally, a minimum of 50% aggregate marks (or equivalent CGPA) is required.\n- **Selection Process**: Admission is based on CAT, XAT, or GMAT scores, followed by MICA's own selection process (GE & PI).\n\n---\n\n### **2. Entrance Exam**\nCandidates need to appear for one of the following entrance exams:\n- **CAT** (Common Admission Test)\n- **XAT** (Xavier Aptitude Test)\n- **GMAT** (Graduate Management Admission Test)\n\nNote: MICA does not conduct its own entrance exam but accepts scores from these exams.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Shortlisting**\n- Based on the entrance exam scores, academic performance, and other criteria, MICA shortlists candidates for the next stage.\n- Shortlisted candidates are invited to participate in the **Group Exercise (GE)** and **Personal Interview (PI)**.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Group Exercise (GE)**\n- The GE is a group activity that assesses communication skills, teamwork, creativity, and problem-solving abilities.\n- Candidates are given a topic or situation to discuss or act upon in a group setting.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Personal Interview (PI)**\n- The PI evaluates the candidate's motivation, understanding of the communications industry, general awareness, and personality traits.\n- Questions may revolve around the candidate's academic background, work experience (if any), hobbies, and aspirations.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Composite Score Calculation**\nMICA calculates a composite score based on:\n- Entrance exam score (CAT/XAT/GMAT)\n- Academic performance\n- Work experience (if applicable)\n- Performance in GE and PI\n\n---\n\n### **7. Final Admission Offer**\n- Based on the composite score, MICA releases a merit list of selected candidates.\n- Candidates who receive admission offers must confirm their acceptance by paying the prescribed fee.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Important Points to Note**\n- **Application Process**: Candidates must fill out the MICA application form online, providing details of their academic background, entrance exam scores, and other required information.\n- **Deadlines**: Keep track of application deadlines for MICA and the respective entrance exams (CAT/XAT/GMAT).\n- **Preparation**: Focus on improving communication skills, general awareness, and creative thinking, as these are crucial for MICA's selection process.\n\n---\n\nBy following these steps and preparing thoroughly, you can enhance your chances of securing admission to MICA, Ahmedabad. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
